{"metadata":{"title":"Advanced Touch Input on iOS","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"roleHeading":"WWDC15","role":"sampleCode"},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC15-233-Advanced-Touch-Input-on-iOS","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sampleCodeDownload":{"kind":"sampleDownload","action":{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc15\/233","overridingTitle":"Watch Video (38 min)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"Low-Latency-Core-Animation","level":2,"text":"Low Latency Core Animation"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The Core animation work starts as soon as the app commits, no need to wait for the next frame to come first","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Done automatically from iOS 9, no extra logic necessary","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Disabled for animations ("},{"code":"CAAnimation","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"s and "},{"code":"UIView","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"’s animations)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Works also with ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/quartzcore\/caeagllayer","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/quartzcore\/cametallayer","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":", in this case you can use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/quartzcore\/cametallayer\/1478157-presentswithtransaction","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" to make sure your metal layer is in sync with your Core Animation layer (otherwise it might happen that the metal layer renders before)","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Touch-Coalescing","level":2,"text":"Touch Coalescing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"From the iPad Air 2, iOS devices ship with a 120-hertz touch scan update rate, this means that devices get twice as much touch events for example when dragging\/drawing."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"iOS will still deliver new touch events at the beginning of a new frame, however you will have access to possibly two touch events instead of just one.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To get those touches, there’s a new API: ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UIEvent"},{"text":"’s ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uievent\/1613808-coalescedtouches"},{"text":", which returns an array of all the coalesced touches since the last time iOS delivered that touch to your app.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Usage example, from:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["for touch in touches {","  let line = lineForTouch(touch)","  addTouchSample(touch, toLine: line)","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"to:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["for touch in touches {","  let line = lineForTouch(touch)","  for coalescedTouch in event.coalescedTouchesForTouch(touch) {","    addTouchSample(coalescedTouch, toLine: line)","  }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Touch-Prediction","level":2,"text":"Touch Prediction"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use this API to get even lower latency in your apps."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"How it works:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"iOS looks at the touches that are delivered to your app, and uses a set of highly tuned algorithms to determine where the user’s finger looks like it’s going at this time","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"And as we get new touch samples, we will update our prediction and deliver new predicted touches to your app"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"New ","type":"text"},{"code":"UIEvent","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" API: ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uievent\/1613814-predictedtouches","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Usage example:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["for touch in touches {","  \/\/ Like before","  let line = lineForTouch(touch)","  for coalescedTouch in event.coalescedTouchesForTouch(touch) {","    addTouchSample(coalescedTouch, toLine: line)","  }","","  \/\/ Remove old predicted touches","  removePredictedSamplesFromLine(line)","","  \/\/ Add new predicted touches","  for predictedTouch in event.predictedTouchesForTouch(touch) {","    addPredictedTouchSample(predictedTouch, toLine: line)","  }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Written-By","level":2,"text":"Written By"},{"type":"row","columns":[{"size":1,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"zntfdr"}]}]},{"size":4,"content":[{"anchor":"Federico-Zanetello","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Federico Zanetello"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/zntfdr","isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Contributed Notes","type":"reference","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Contributed Notes"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"|"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/zntfdr","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"|"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/zntfd